<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1883-01-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1883-01-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="464" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d464">
                    <head>No. 465.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Francis</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Frelinghuysen</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Lisbon</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1883-01-08"><hi rend="italic">January</hi> 8, 1883</date>.
                            (Received January 27.)</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 23.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to transmit herewith a
                        summary of the Portuguese budget for the fiscal year 1883–1884, as presented
                        to the Cortes by Señor Fontes, minister of finance, on the 5th instant. The
                        items embrace estimates for the year and indicate a deficit in the receipts
                        to cover expenditures of a comparatively small amount, greatly less than in
                        any former year for a long time back.</p>
                    <p>Another report by the minister of finance not yet submitted to the Cortes
                        will show the present condition of the treasury and the amount of the
                        floating debt.</p>
                    <p>The present debt of Portugal is about $435,000,000, upon which annual
                        interest of about $14,000,000 is paid. I do not give the precise sums for
                        the reason that no official statements of them have been made, but the
                        amounts named very nearly approximate to the fact.</p>
                    <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                    <closer><signed>JOHN M. FRANCIS.</signed></closer>
                    <frus:attachment>
